<div type="definition">
<p>FLAVOUR RESEMBLING that of SUGAR.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The current standard word for sweetness is gān 甘, and the word strongly connotes pleasantness of taste rather than just sugary flavour.</p>
<p>2. Tián 甜 is rare and denotes sugary sweet flavour as such.</p>
        </div>
